-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">März 15, 2023</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104efs1665702919398.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/efs1665702919398.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/efs1665702919398.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"efs1665702919398\" role=\"article\">\n<div class=\"body refbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Information (connector characteristics).\n </p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"efs1665702919398__section_N10019_N10016_N10001\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d763179e50\">Modes</h2>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"efs1665702919398__li_d52877e1_d52878e1_d52879e1\">Mode 0—provides Uniface with DBMS and connector\n               characteristics. The mode 0 Info request must be successful. The Info request can be\n               called several times, although identical characteristics should be returned for each\n               call.</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"efs1665702919398__li_d52880e1_d52881e1_d52882e1\">Mode 1—provides Uniface with the user name and\n               password corresponding to the current logon path. If the connector is not capable of\n               providing logon information, this can be unsuccessful. This request is called when\n               there is a reference to <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$user</span> or <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$password</span> in\n               ProcScript language.</li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"efs1665702919398__section_N10038_N10016_N10001\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d763179e71\">Conditions</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"efs1665702919398__p_d152240e1_d152241e1_d152242e1\">When the Info request is called in mode 1, there is a current logon path.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"efs1665702919398__section_N10046_N10016_N10001\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d763179e80\">Description</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"efs1665702919398__p_d152246e1_d152247e1_d152248e1\">This request provides Uniface with DBMS and connector characteristics, or supplies logon information.</p>\n<div class=\"div\"> Refer to: <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"zge1665702663349.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/zge1665702663349.html\" title=\"Uniface allows you to access data in multiple DBMSs in a uniform way, simultaneously. The term DBMS is used generically here to describe any structured form of data storage that Uniface understands. According to this definition, a record management system is also a DBMS. All the actions carried out on database tables or files occur via the DBMS interface.\">Uniface Database I/O</a>\n</div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2527121\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2527121\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "I Info Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated März 15, 2023 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Information (connector characteristics). Modes Mode 0—provides Uniface with DBMS and connector characteristics. The mode 0 Info request must be successful. The Info request can be called several times, although identical characteristics should be returned for each call. Mode 1—provides Uniface with the user name and password corresponding to the current logon path. If the connector is not capable of providing logon information, this can be unsuccessful. This request is called when there is a reference to $user or $password in ProcScript language. Conditions When the Info request is called in mode 1, there is a current logon path. Description This request provides Uniface with DBMS and connector characteristics, or supplies logon information. Refer to: Uniface Database I/O Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}